<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="418" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1029,2028]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,513,1101,1127]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">
Remarks on 
<typeStatus box="[353,404,1101,1127]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">type</typeStatus>
material
</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Vanhoffen, E." box="[527,726,1101,1127]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" pagination="447 - 598" refId="ref26325" refString="Vanhoffen, E. (1914) Die Isopoden der Deutschen Sudpolar Expedition 1901 - 1903. Deutsche Sudpolar Expedition, 15, 447 - 598. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10649" type="journal article" year="1914">Vanhöffen (1914)</bibRefCitation>
only illustrated a single female specimen that he referred to as “ 
<typeStatus box="[162,217,1137,1163]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">type</typeStatus>
”; we identified this specimen based on the configuration of the body and a missing flagellum on the antenna. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Vanhoffen, E." box="[265,513,1173,1200]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" pagination="447 - 598" refId="ref26325" refString="Vanhoffen, E. (1914) Die Isopoden der Deutschen Sudpolar Expedition 1901 - 1903. Deutsche Sudpolar Expedition, 15, 447 - 598. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10649" type="journal article" year="1914">Vanhöffen (1914:574)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that only 
<specimenCount box="[741,880,1173,1200]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" type="generic">7 specimens</specimenCount>
were present, 2 vials from Gauss station 5I02 (
<date pageId="17" pageNumber="418" value="1902-01-05">5 January 1902</date>
) were found in the collection, and the vial containing his illustrated female specimen (also illustrated herein) had 
<specimenCount box="[283,423,1245,1271]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" type="generic">8 specimens</specimenCount>
, 2 of which were mancas. We suspect that he overlooked one of the mancas when counting. Another vial in 
<accessionNumber box="[326,462,1281,1308]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/ZMB17711" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">ZMB 17711</accessionNumber>
from the same Gauss station 5I02 (date 
<date box="[910,1080,1281,1308]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" value="1902-01-05">5 January 1902</date>
) contained an ovigerous female and an adult male, both of which are illustrated here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
