. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Vanhoffen, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Vanhoffen" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[293,772,1944,1968]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paramunnidae" genus="Meridiosignum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerguelensis">
<emphasis box="[293,580,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Meridiosignum kerguelensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vanhoffen, E." box="[592,765,1944,1968]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" pagination="447 - 598" refId="ref26325" refString="Vanhoffen, E. (1914) Die Isopoden der Deutschen Sudpolar Expedition 1901 - 1903. Deutsche Sudpolar Expedition, 15, 447 - 598. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10649" type="journal article" year="1914">Vanhöffen, 1914</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, A, lectotype, ♀, 5, 6, 7, pereionite 5–7 lateral margins and coxae. B (all other figs.), paralectotype, copulatory ♂; e, eyestalk; pl1, pleopod I, pl2, pleopod II, p1, pereiopod I; p2, pereiopod II; p7 lateral margin and coxa of pereionite 7; ur, uropod. Scale for habitus, 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
